i e dell’Identità Siciliana\" src=\"ISic020380-thumb.jpg\">\u003C/a>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"apparatus\">\u003Ch4>Apparatus criticus\u003C/h4>\u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan>  \u003Cspan>Text after Biondi 1992\u003C/span>  \u003C/span>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"translation\">\u003Ch2>English translation\u003C/h2>\u003Cp class=\"translation-author\">  \u003C/p>\u003Cp>  \u003C/p>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"translation\">\u003Ch2>Italian translation\u003C/h2>\u003Cp class=\"translation-author\">  \u003C/p>\u003Cp>  \u003C/p>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"commentary\">\u003Ch2>commentary\u003C/h2>  \u003Cp>Cross-shaped sign recurrent as a mark throughout the ancient world. Cf. Agostiniani 1977, p.11, which reports some parallels with Attic ceramic: Graef, Langlotz 1933, p.128, no.1523, N 456; Milne 1936, fig. 34, no.14; F.Xanthos IV, p.174, nos. 400-401. The sign is very common in the Elymian corpus from Grotta Vanella (see records from \u003Ca href=\"http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic020008\" target=\"_blank\">ISic020008\u003C/a> to \u003Ca href=\"http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic020035\" target=\"_blank\">ISic020035\u003C/a>).\u003C/p>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"bibliography\">\u003Ch2>bibliography\u003C/h2>  \u003Cul>\u003Cli> Biondi 1992 117, no. 2, pl. III.2 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002322\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002322\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003Cli> Agostiniani 2021 380 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002320\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002320\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>  \u003Cul>\u003Cli> Graef, Langlotz 1933 p.128, no.1523, N 456 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002563\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002563\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003Cli> Milne 1936 fig. 34, no.14 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002564\" target=\"_blank\">https://bibli